The Senzo Meyiwa murder trial continues this morning. Sergeant Thabo Mosia, the first state witness, is still undergoing cross-examination by the Defence. PRETORIA - The trial against five men accused of killing Senzo Meyiwa continues on Thursday. On Wednesday, Forensic Officer Thabo Mosia told the High Court in Pretoria that the crime scene was a bit challenging and he needed reinforcements. Mosia is the first witness to testify in the trial.